data.text:
@AlchemistBBQ @doctorcomics @loganbonner @qh_murphy I love the idea of opponents cirlcling, blades flashing, the "dance of death".

In 1st ed, this was narratively assumed - yet wholly ignored.

AoOs and express mini req't brought this to life. Elimination of facing= too far? But foregoing an attack(s) to move was the killer.

@qh_murphy There was ALWAYS more combat maneuvering at level 1-5 in 3.x/PF1. Swashbucklers, in particular, were dramatically different to play at lower levels.

As soon as movement gave up that extra attack - let alone 2 extra attacks, the 5 Foot Shuffle Reigned supreme.

In PF2, MAP helps.
